  "text": "As far as we know, only two other manipulations have demonstrated reverse directions of developmental trends in false memories. [CITATION_1] showed that false memories for a category exemplar increased with age when several exemplars of that category were studied, but decreased when only one exemplar was studied. [CITATION_2] and [CITATION_3] found that false memories increase with age for associative lists but decrease for phonological lists.",
